parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or break down, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Catalytic converter failure can cause the vehicle to catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: flames shooting out of the center of the car

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oxygen sensor failure can cause the vehicle to run poorly, leading to decreased performance and potential safety issues.
symptoms: loses acceleration when attempting to pass.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Seatbelt failure can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Driver side seatbelt harness has shredded over time and is no longer usable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Carburetor failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of control, especially at high RPM, which can result in accidents. Additionally, stalling in traffic can increase the risk of rear-end collisions.
Fuel pump failure can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: the fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or catch on fire, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle cuts off while driving
electrical shorts or faults in the dashboard or engine.
